history.content: I believe you can still apply. I submitted my application last week after the deadline and they gave me the offer in two days.

children.subject:
The faculty have their budgets for the spring, so they can now make their choices about GSIs and readers. Many choose their GSIs first, but not all of them, so you should get your reader application in now if you're interested. For upper division EE courses, you could also send them an e-mail and ask whether they are looking for a reader, cc'ing me. If that faculty member isn't, I can steer you toward someone who is.

Heather (heather@berkeley.edu)

history.content: I am wondering does the reader position of next semester EE upper-division classes goes out quickly? I notice the priority deadline has passed, yet I wonder whether I still hold a chance?
